Remark has its own model ('model/remark/').

Enhance data encapsulation and align with the domain model.

Match the other fields of Person.

Introduce a new Predicate class,
RemarkContainsKeyphrasePredicate.java,
in the seedu.realodex.model.person package.

This class is similar to NameContainsKeyphrasePredicate.
Facilitates the filtering of Person instances
based on whether their remark contains a specified keyphrase,
enhancing the application's filter function.
The predicate performs a case-insensitive check
to ensure user-friendly search functionality.

The FilterCommand predicate was of
type NameContainsKeyphrasePredicate.

This modification allows the command
to apply a wider variety of conditions
for filtering Person objects,
thereby increasing its utility in various contexts.

Refactor the FilterCommand within the application
to utilize a generic Predicate<Person> interface.

The change facilitates the introduction of
more complex filtering criteria
without necessitating additional modifications
to the FilterCommand's underlying implementation.

The `FilterCommand` only supports filtering by name

Incorporating remark-based filtering
expands the command's functionality,
allowing users to refine searches with remark criteria.

Extend `FilterCommand` functionality
to include remark-based filtering criteria,
by creating a general Predicate<Person>

To do:
* Further refactoring to encapsulate predicate logic
within the `ArgMap` class, enhancing code readability.
*  Evaluate and abstract common validation checks
within FilterCommandParser.java
* Refine parsing logic to distinguish between
empty and non-empty remark filters effectively.
(Currently `n/james r/ works`)

Refactor getValue and getRemarkValue into
the same method by checking for PREFIX_REMARK

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor out creation of individual predicates
commitResults.messageBody:
In producePredicate, created new individual
predicate creators to keep the method
more readable as well as scalable as we filter
by more fields in future

Create and refactor
NameContainsKeyphrasePredicate,
RemarkContainsKeyphrasePredicate,
into the package for better OOP and scalability
where we can add more predicates in future

The creation of predicates is done in the
FilterCommandParser class which will get
too long as we add more functionality to filter

Introduce a new PredicateProducer class,
which is suitably added in the Predicate package class.
This class centralises the creation of predicates
based on its respective prefixes
(i.e. PREFIX_NAME, PREFIX_REMARK)

Centralising predicate creation enhances
code readability, maintainability, and scalability.

The parsing logic in the application is
intermingled with prefix checking
in the Filter command parsing logic.
This leads to a convoluted parsing process.

Introduce the PrefixChecker class within the
seedu.realodex.logic.parser package.
This class abstracts the logic for checking
the presence and uniqueness of prefixes
in user input, thereby decoupling
prefix validation from the main parsing logic.

By centralising prefix checking into a
dedicated class, the parsing components
are simplified and made more modular.
This enhancement promotes code reuse,
improves readability, and facilitates easier maintenance.

The possible prefixes are repeated many times
as arguments in the prefixChecker as well as
the initial tokeniser input

Consolidate these possible prefixes
into an array so that it is easily scalable
and improve readability of code

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug for validation in empty remark prefix
commitResults.messageBody:
Implementation treats input with a
non-empty 'n/' (name) prefix alongside
an empty 'r/' (remark) prefix as valid.

However, the command should be actually
returning an error for having
more than one prefix present.

Modify the command validation logic
to ensure that an empty 'r/' (remark) prefix
is correctly identified as invalid input.
This involves enhancing the prefix presence
check to differentiate between truly present
prefixes (with non-empty values) and
those that are syntactically present
but lack content.

checkNoDuplicatePrefix logic is now handled in
the PrefixChecker class

With new predicate types being introduced,
add new testing for Filter Commands.

Make new tests for the methods in prefix checker
to ensure that they work as expected.

Create new tests for RemarkContainsKeyphrase
predicate class as well as refine tests in
NameContainsKeyphrase predicate test cases
